Text.SourceString: Yesterday was the most beautiful day of my life, <PlayerName>$player</>.//You were radiant, the embodiment of all my dreams come true.
Text.LocalizedString: Yesterday was the most beautiful day of my life, <PlayerName>$player</>.//You were radiant, the embodiment of all my dreams come true.

Text.SourceString: I'm a lucky soul.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm a lucky soul.

Text.SourceString: Good morning, my love! I've prepared a breakfast for you.//<portrait=normal>It's important to me that you start your day well-fed and happy.
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, my love! I've prepared a breakfast for you.//<portrait=normal>It's important to me that you start your day well-fed and happy.

Text.SourceString: Thought I'd play chef and whip up something for you.//I hope you like it, my love.
Text.LocalizedString: Thought I'd play chef and whip up something for you.//I hope you like it, my love.

Text.SourceString: Looks like the rain's pouring down again. Fancy a game of puddle-jumping?//<portrait=happy>The one who jumps the furthest gets to pick the movie tonight!
Text.LocalizedString: Looks like the rain's pouring down again. Fancy a game of puddle-jumping?//<portrait=happy>The one who jumps the furthest gets to pick the movie tonight!

Text.SourceString: The rain is really coming down, isn't it?//<portrait=happy>How about a cozy indoor picnic with hot cocoa and stories?
Text.LocalizedString: The rain is really coming down, isn't it?//<portrait=happy>How about a cozy indoor picnic with hot cocoa and stories?

Text.SourceString: I think we both could use some warmth.
Text.LocalizedString: I think we both could use some warmth.

Text.SourceString: I can't help but be amazed at the snow.//It transforms everything, makes it feel magical.
Text.LocalizedString: I can't help but be amazed at the snow.//It transforms everything, makes it feel magical.

Text.SourceString: But the most magical part of today? Being here with you.
Text.LocalizedString: But the most magical part of today? Being here with you.

Text.SourceString: It's a snow day, love!
Text.LocalizedString: It's a snow day, love!

Text.SourceString: Everything is covered in a blanket of white.
Text.LocalizedString: Everything is covered in a blanket of white.

Text.SourceString: I'm incredibly grateful for the day I adopted Taco from <NpcName>Suki</>.//<portrait=happy>It's nice knowing he's keeping mom company and she's not feeling too lonely.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm incredibly grateful for the day I adopted Taco from <NpcName>Suki</>.//<portrait=happy>It's nice knowing he's keeping mom company and she's not feeling too lonely.

Text.SourceString: Living out here on the farm has been a real eye-opener.//<portrait=normal>It's not just the peace and quiet, it's also about feeling connected to the land and the food we eat.
Text.LocalizedString: Living out here on the farm has been a real eye-opener.//<portrait=normal>It's not just the peace and quiet, it's also about feeling connected to the land and the food we eat.

Text.SourceString: It's similar to the vineyard, but we didn't grow much of anything but grapes there.//<portrait=normal>And we didn't eat them...they went straight into wine bottles.
Text.LocalizedString: It's similar to the vineyard, but we didn't grow much of anything but grapes there.//<portrait=normal>And we didn't eat them...they went straight into wine bottles.

Text.SourceString: Promise me you won't work too hard today?//I don't want you to get sick, my love.
Text.LocalizedString: Promise me you won't work too hard today?//I don't want you to get sick, my love.

Text.SourceString: Our house looks absolutely amazing.//I love your taste in decor.
Text.LocalizedString: Our house looks absolutely amazing.//I love your taste in decor.

Text.SourceString: I was thinking of visiting my parents later.//<portrait=surprised>Hey, love, do we have any jam? I want to bring some over for Mother.
Text.LocalizedString: I was thinking of visiting my parents later.//<portrait=surprised>Hey, love, do we have any jam? I want to bring some over for Mother.

Text.SourceString: She's a big fan of jam, especially the ones you make!
Text.LocalizedString: She's a big fan of jam, especially the ones you make!

Text.SourceString: Mother was telling me the other day how much she adores you.//<portrait=normal>It makes me so happy to see how well you get along with my family, even my dad.
Text.LocalizedString: Mother was telling me the other day how much she adores you.//<portrait=normal>It makes me so happy to see how well you get along with my family, even my dad.

Text.SourceString: Let's face it, he has a unique personality that not everyone appreciates.
Text.LocalizedString: Let's face it, he has a unique personality that not everyone appreciates.

Text.SourceString: I've always had a fondness for this place, even when it was abandoned.//Sometimes, I would come here just to appreciate the view.
Text.LocalizedString: I've always had a fondness for this place, even when it was abandoned.//Sometimes, I would come here just to appreciate the view.

Text.SourceString: Of course, now that you're here with me, I love it even more.
Text.LocalizedString: Of course, now that you're here with me, I love it even more.

Text.SourceString: Do we need anything from Sam's, love?//<portrait=normal>I can head into town later and pick them up for us.
Text.LocalizedString: Do we need anything from Sam's, love?//<portrait=normal>I can head into town later and pick them up for us.

Text.SourceString: Come here, you... Why do you look so good today?
Text.LocalizedString: Come here, you... Why do you look so good today?
